# NetworkCompatibilityToken.Compatibility.sessionProtocolVersionMismatch

**Case**

An indication that two peers running incompatible versions of RealityKit can’t sync.

## Declaration

```swift
case sessionProtocolVersionMismatch
```

## Discussion

The [doc://com.apple.RealityKit/documentation/RealityKit/NetworkCompatibilityToken/compatibilityWith(_:)] method returns this value when two devices have different OS versions and there has been a significant change in networking protocol between those releases.

## Compatibility indicators

- **NetworkCompatibilityToken.Compatibility.compatible**: An indication that the compared devices are running compatible versions of RealityKit.
